column5: I caught this yesterday and am stumped as to what it is.  It has the spots of a brown but could also be a speckled or a rainbow?  It was caught on the Sydenham river if that helps.
That is a rainbow trout. Juveniles have those big spots around lateral line.
Yup, rainbow smolt.  If you are catching lots of them, you should probably move.  Those are future steelhead
